In Firefox, the error will be: {{Exception: TypeError: j is null}}
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Access the instance
 # Ensure the profile is set to another language, such as Russian or French
 # Go to {{[http://xx/secure/RapidBoard.jspa?rapidView=324]}}
 # Error will be thrown

h3. Expected Results

No error will be thrown
h3. Actual Results

Following error is thrown
 !Selection_360.png|thumbnail!
h3. Notes
{panel}
This is a bug in localisation.
Instead of having Unicode for
{noformat}
1<{noformat}
which is:
{code:java}
1\u003c
{code}
Instead, it has XML/HTML value for that:
{code:java}
1&lt;
{code}
{panel}
h3. Workaround

To use the default English for the time being

The JSON object the webhook sends contains this for the Sprint customfield:
{noformat}"customfield_10020": [
        "com.atlassian.greenhopper.service.sprint.Sprint@4ccd3f[id=2,rapidViewId=6,state=FUTURE,name=TIB Sprint 2,goal=<null>,startDate=<null>,endDate=<null>,completeDate=<null>,sequence=2]"
      ],
{noformat}
Looks like it's just printing the toString() of the Java object instead of serialising it to a proper JSON object. Would be good if this return a JSON object.

Currently it is possible to collapse all Swimlanes under Active Sprints using the hotkey *_-_*.

 

For customer who are planning several sprints at the same time, or have large backlogs, it would be helpful to extend this shortcut to the Backlog page as well. Currently they have to collapse every sprint they are not planning whenever the page is refreshed, which can be annoying when planning large numbers of sprints.

 

From a support case: 
{quote}
As I groom the backlog, I am having to scroll up and down and review stories from different future sprints to move things around its cumbersome and inefficient to individually collapse each future sprint each time I do refresh. 
{quote}
